body_html:
I see.
Maybe there is something going on with my installation. I did I try to upgrade (with pip install --upgrade tensorflow) I get:
Requirement already up-to-date: tensorflow in d:\anaconda2\envs\tensorflow\lib\site-packages (1.11.0rc2)
When I print tf.version I get 1.10
and when I print tf.file i get the correct location:
D:\Anaconda2\envs\tensorflow\lib\site-packages\tensorflow\__init__.py

Edit: A rookie mistake, had two version of Tensorflow at the same time. Upgrading to 1.11.0rc2 solved it.

Thank you

body:
I see. 
Maybe there is something going on with my installation. I did I try to upgrade (with pip install --upgrade tensorflow)  I get: 
`Requirement already up-to-date: tensorflow in d:\anaconda2\envs\tensorflow\lib\site-packages (1.11.0rc2)`
When I print tf.__version__ I get 1.10
and when I print tf.__file__ i get the correct location: 
`D:\Anaconda2\envs\tensorflow\lib\site-packages\tensorflow\__init__.py`

**Edit**: A rookie mistake, had two version of Tensorflow at the same time. Upgrading to 1.11.0rc2 solved it.

Thank you
